HEADWORD: Coreopsis
<hw>Co`re*op"sis</hw> <pr>(k⟦omac⟧`r⟦esl⟧*⟦ocr⟧p"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>ko`ris</grk> bug +
<grk>'o`psis</grk> appearance.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
herbaceous composite plants, having the achenes two-horned and remotely
resembling some insect; tickseed. <spn>Coreopsis tinctoria</spn>, of the
Western plains, the commonest plant of the genus, has been used in
dyeing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

